  "prompt": "How do I play gem TD in DOTA2 when there is no internet?",
  "response": "DOTA 2's Gem TD, like many custom games, typically requires an internet connection to access the DOTA 2 Workshop and download the game files. If you're looking to play Gem TD offline, you would need to first ensure that you have the custom game downloaded while you still have internet access.\n\nHere\u2019s a step-by-step guide to play Gem TD or similar custom games offline:\n\n1. **Download the Custom Game:**\n   - Open DOTA 2 while you have an internet connection.\n   - Go to the \"Play\" tab and select \"Find a Match.\"\n   - Choose \"Custom Games\" and search for Gem TD.\n   - Subscribe to the game, and it will start downloading.\n\n2. **Launch the Game:**\n   - After the custom game has downloaded, you can launch DOTA 2 while still connected to the internet and create a lobby with the Gem TD mode.\n   - This way, the game files are saved locally on your system.\n\n3. **Playing Offline:**\n   - Once you have started the custom game with internet access at least once, you can then switch to offline mode.\n   - Launch DOTA 2, go to your library, and switch to Offline Mode in Steam.\n   - Go to the \"Play\" tab again, and you should see the custom game you downloaded under \"Custom Games.\"\n   - You can then start a lobby and play the game offline as long as it does not require any online features.\n\nKeep in mind that some features of custom games might not function properly offline if they rely on online connectivity for core mechanics or updates. \n\nIf you encounter any issues, check for community forums or support related to Gem TD, as there may be specific instructions or considerations for offline play.",
